This paper is about pruning convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to reduce their computation and storage requirements. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and data structures (cs.DS). Given that the paper focuses on CNNs and their compression, it is most likely to belong to cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.DS.
